title: Matt Gaetz
added: On March 30, 2021, [[Axios (website)|''Axios'']] reported that Gaetz was "seriously considering not seeking re-election and possibly leaving Congress early for a job at [[Newsmax]]".<ref>{{Cite web|last=Treene|first=Alayna|title=Rep. Matt Gaetz eyes early retirement from Congress to take job at Newsmax|url=https://www.axios.com/matt-gaetz-retirement-congress-newsmax-e1a0e6bb-0279-4e97-ab22-508e28f4347a.html|access-date=2021-03-30|website=Axios|language=en}}</ref> This report came out hours before it was announced that Gaetz was being investigated for a relationship he had with a 17-year old girl.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Schmidt|first=Michael S.|last2=Benner|first2=Katie|date=2021-03-30|title=Matt Gaetz Is Said to Be Investigated Over Possible Sexual Relationship With a Girl, 17|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/03/30/us/politics/matt-gaetz-sex-trafficking-investigation.html|access-date=2021-03-30|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

title: Matt Gaetz
added: Gaetz sent [[Axios]] screenshots of text messages, emails and documents outlining the alleged extortion scheme, which he claimed was being run by former DOJ employee David McGee.In an interview with [[Tucker Carlson]] in responding to the allegations he stated that "I am demanding the [[Department of Justice]] and [[FBI]] release the audio recordings that were made under their supervision and at their direction which will prove my innocence" referring to an audio recording between his father and David McGee, the former DOJ Official Gaetz claimed to have been in an extortion scheme. He furthered that the claims of an underage sexual relationship could be proven false by travel records<ref>{{cite web|author=Tucker Carlson|website=Youtube|title=Matt Gaetz responds to sex trafficking allegations on 'Tucker Carlson Tonight'|date= March 30, 2021|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PQzLCHLle-g}}</ref> McGee told The Daily Beast the reports of extortion were "completely, totally false." and that they were to distract from his investigation into whether he violated sex trafficking laws.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/former-doj-official-says-gaetz-claim-of-extortion-are-false-2021-3|title='Completely, totally false': Former DOJ official says Gaetz's claim of extortion is to distract from investigation|author=Sarah Al-Arshani|website=Business Insider|date=March 30, 2021}}</ref>
